JOHANNEBURG – Canadian crooner Michael Bublé enjoyed pranking shoppers in London by disguising himself as a South African shop assistant named Dion. After undergoing a makeover, Bublé begins engaging with shoppers, sporting a South African accent that comes close. At one stage, he even has a dig at himself saying, “Maybe because it’s Christmas, maybe he’s going to come out of his cave or something,” to which a shopper replied, “I wish.” Watch the video above to for the full insert. YouTube